              "label": "Original File - 134 MB",
              "format": "image/tiff"
            }
          ],
          "annotations": [
            {
              "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p33n2113j/canvas/p3/annopage",
              "type": "AnnotationPage",
              "items": [
                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p33n2113j/manifest/annotation/p3",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>I think we shall not differ much in our<lb/> notions about “Reforms”.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I hear that <persName>Mr. Nathan</persName> (the revd.) has<lb/>\n                left <placeName>St Thomas</placeName>, &amp; gone to <placeName>Jamaica</placeName>\n                to settle<lb/> up his business with his brother in law with<lb/> whom he was in\n                partnership &amp; that he (<persName>Nathan</persName>)<lb/> will not return to\n                    <placeName>St Thomas</placeName>. What's in the wind?<lb/> I have recd no\n                letters from him for a long time past.<lb/> We continue to worship regularly in the\n                rooms temporarily<lb/> prepared &amp; have an excellent “<hi rend=\"underline\"\n                    >Siphar</hi>” tho' small<lb/> which we can keep as long as I please.</p>\n            <p>Between ourselves I doubt if the few who attend service<lb/> will continue after I\n                leave here. If the yellow<lb/> fever is not prevalent in the summer I would\n                like<lb/> to return &amp; consecrate the synagogue for the New Year.<lb/> Of this\n                more anon.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Hoping that you may enjoy our approaching<lb/> festival &amp; be\n                well to perform all your duties at the<lb/> convention</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">I am as ever sincerely</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">your friend</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(4)\"><persName role=\"author\">G. Kursheedt</persName>.</p>\n            <p>Will you be kind enough to offer my fondest<lb/> love to my dear Aunt &amp; husband\n                &amp; tell them<lb/> that I hope to visit them for a day or so ere very<lb/> long,\n                as I have concluded to order the chandelier bracket &amp;c for<lb/> the gas to be\n                used in the Synagogue, from your city &amp; shall desire to explain to<lb/>\n                <persName>Mr Cornelius</persName> precisely what I want.</p>\n        </body>\n    </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p33n2113j/canvas/p3"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
